        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I was looking for an HTTP based JSON-RPC client that easily hooked into Zend_Json_Server.  At first, I thought it might already be included as part of Zend_Http_Client, but I couldn't find anything specifically for it.  The core of it seems trivial in nature, though I'd suspect one would want the same results as Zend_Soap_Client and Zend_Rest_Client.\n\nI have attached an example of Zend_Json_Client.  Pretty bare bones stuff which relies on __call(), Zend_Json, and Zend_Http_Client to accomplish simple tasks such as:\n\n$client = new Zend_Json_Client($jsonRpcUri);\n$result = $client->getSqrt(9.0);\necho $result; \/\/ 3.0\n\nI apologize if this has already been done elsewhere and my research missed it.  I just thought it would be nice to have a JSON-RPC as a local interface experience."
        },
